  "label": "Gloamslate Sleeping Alcove",
  "description": "Gloamslate Sleeping Alcove forms a low recess cut into the basaltcrete flat, its mouth sealed by ash-gaskets that trap fine grit in layered seams. A narrow cot-frame is bolted to the back wall beneath a canopy of conduit shielding plates, their Imperial stencils bleached and scored by windborne abrasion. The sole lumen strip reaches the space through soot-stained baffles, reducing illumination to a bruise-toned half-light that emphasizes the alcove’s cramped depth. Vent grilles are fitted with coarse particulate screens, and the decking lip is chipped smooth by repeated passage and equipment drag.",
